msContents.summary: Extensive collection of medical texts compiled in 1500-1501 during medical studies in Bologna. Contents include copies of texts in the medical curriculum, the most substantial being al-Rāzī's Nonus Almansoris and Avicenna's Canon, and at least one, Paolo Bagellardo's Libellus de egritudinibus infancium, copied from a printed edition. Lists of prescriptions dated 1477 to 1501 also present. Marginal commentary and notes and interlinear glosses and annotations. Numerous smaller leaves bound in, especially in the sections concerning prescriptions.
msContents.textLang: Latin, with one work in German (f. 167r-167v)

layoutDesc.layout: Nonus Almansoris (f. 12r-160v) written in up to 20 long lines in a larger script, with interspersed sections of commentary and interlinear and marginal notes in a smaller script; other works vary.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in hybrid script by Johannes Mellarinus (f. 193v, 402v).

binding.p: Contemporary (early 16th-century) parchment; title written on spine in ink.
